00:20:42,735 --> 00:20:44,934
- The accident might have been... - It's not true.

273
00:20:44,935 --> 00:20:46,771
caused by the victim's negligence.

274
00:20:47,465 --> 00:20:49,073
- After drinking, - I know it's not true.

275
00:20:49,074 --> 00:20:51,174
he walks through the turnstile...

276
00:20:51,175 --> 00:20:52,571
without calling the station office.

277
00:20:53,044 --> 00:20:54,644
Then he walks into the station office...

278
00:20:54,645 --> 00:20:57,226
and grabs the keys without asking for permission first.

279
00:20:57,274 --> 00:21:00,013
The guy who died at the subway station was drunk.

280
00:21:00,014 --> 00:21:02,024
- Seriously? My gosh. - Yes.

281
00:21:02,715 --> 00:21:04,154
That's why he fell into the tracks?

282
00:21:04,155 --> 00:21:06,083
May I see that for a second? I'm sorry.

283
00:21:06,084 --> 00:21:07,724
Many are pointing out that the company...

284
00:21:07,725 --> 00:21:10,611
should've followed the protocols on safety and employee management.

285
00:21:13,225 --> 00:21:14,315
- Here you go. - Thank you.

286
00:21:17,294 --> 00:21:19,650
I told you that we have to look into it more.

287
00:21:20,135 --> 00:21:21,503
We don't know if he actually drank,

288
00:21:21,504 --> 00:21:23,273
if it was an accident caused by a safety issue,

289
00:21:23,274 --> 00:21:24,835
or if it happened because of an illness.

290
00:21:25,375 --> 00:21:27,791
Forget it. Just put him on the phone.

291
00:21:28,244 --> 00:21:29,295
Put him on the phone!

292
00:21:30,044 --> 00:21:31,402
Darn it.

293
00:21:32,915 --> 00:21:34,343
This is Gong Il Sun from UDC.

294
00:21:34,344 --> 00:21:37,822
An expert must look into this case.

295
00:21:38,185 --> 00:21:40,326
You'll only transfer disease-related cases to us?

296
00:21:40,725 --> 00:21:43,694
Sir, we can't find out whether it was caused by an illness...

297
00:21:43,695 --> 00:21:45,154
without the investigation rights...

298
00:21:46,425 --> 00:21:47,515
Gosh.

299
00:21:49,834 --> 00:21:51,093
(Flawed safety systems.)

300
00:21:51,094 --> 00:21:52,941
(Possibility of exposure to toxic substances)

301
00:22:09,215 --> 00:22:10,953
I made Mr. Suk work overnight.

302
00:22:10,954 --> 00:22:13,402
To analyze the substances from Hanil SD.

303
00:22:15,255 --> 00:22:17,224
This is a thesis on the cause of neural paralysis...

304
00:22:17,225 --> 00:22:19,000
regarding laborer sanitation issues.

305
00:22:19,594 --> 00:22:20,992
How did you know this was your seat?

306
00:22:24,194 --> 00:22:25,766
Oh, my. Sorry.

307
00:22:28,735 --> 00:22:30,074
He didn't drink alcohol.

308
00:22:30,075 --> 00:22:33,403
I'm certain there was a water bottle inside his backpack too.

309
00:22:33,404 --> 00:22:36,638
They're just thinking he drank soju because of the circumstances.

310
00:22:37,414 --> 00:22:39,729
You brat. You never give me a chance to talk.

311
00:22:40,245 --> 00:22:41,468
You'll start work here, right?

312
00:22:41,884 --> 00:22:44,230
Your salary goes up annually, and you're a 2nd level official.

313
00:22:44,454 --> 00:22:45,724
Let me warn you beforehand.

314
00:22:45,725 --> 00:22:47,284
I can't guarantee you'll work less than 40 hours a week.

315
00:22:47,285 --> 00:22:49,804
But instead, I'll make sure you get paid for overtime.

316
00:22:50,424 --> 00:22:52,024
Your position will be a team leader...

317
00:22:52,025 --> 00:22:53,320
It's an addiction.

318
00:22:54,295 --> 00:22:56,663
What? Addicted to work? Me?

319
00:22:56,664 --> 00:22:58,804
Ha Rang. I have a hunch.

320
00:22:58,805 --> 00:23:00,363
Not only was there a lack of a safety system,

321
00:23:00,364 --> 00:23:02,834
but he probably had a disease due to toxic substances.

322
00:23:02,835 --> 00:23:03,895
Okay.

323
00:23:04,775 --> 00:23:06,375
Then what's on your mind?

324
00:23:06,704 --> 00:23:09,602
An organic solvent. There was a detergent he used often.

325
00:23:09,644 --> 00:23:11,943
It's isopropyl alcohol. Ruled out.

326
00:23:11,944 --> 00:23:13,084
That was an assumption.

327
00:23:13,085 --> 00:23:15,014
It might be another type of detergent.

328
00:23:15,015 --> 00:23:17,383
Okay. We need to rule out the fact that he drank first.

329
00:23:17,384 --> 00:23:19,084
But how? The whole nation...

330
00:23:19,085 --> 00:23:21,329
thinks he drank soju during work and got in an accident.

331
00:23:24,894 --> 00:23:27,985
You can't even drink much. What did you drink for?

332
00:23:28,124 --> 00:23:30,583
What? Are you saying you're a grown-up now?

333
00:23:34,035 --> 00:23:35,504
He can't drink.

334
00:23:35,505 --> 00:23:37,774
He was born with a lack of enzymes that can break down alcohol.

335
00:23:37,775 --> 00:23:40,325
There's no way he would drink soju before going to work.

336
00:23:40,545 --> 00:23:42,310
There's no way to prove that.

337
00:23:42,515 --> 00:23:43,544
Ruled out.

338
00:23:43,545 --> 00:23:45,843
TL Medical Center is probably keeping Ha Rang's blood.

339
00:23:45,844 --> 00:23:47,925
His blood alcohol-level will be 0 percent.

340
00:23:48,715 --> 00:23:51,102
That jerk Moh Sung Kuk will cover up everything.

341
00:23:52,525 --> 00:23:54,086
Is this real?

342
00:23:54,684 --> 00:23:56,324
"The chief of UDC..."

343
00:23:56,325 --> 00:23:58,494
"shall carry out an epidemiological survey for substances or..."

344
00:23:58,495 --> 00:24:01,193
"diseases that may threaten the people without hesitation."

345
00:24:01,194 --> 00:24:03,034
"No one shall refuse or interrupt this process..."

346
00:24:03,035 --> 00:24:04,534
"without a justifiable reason."

347
00:24:04,535 --> 00:24:05,727
Is this real?

348
00:24:06,204 --> 00:24:08,034
Of course, it's real.

349
00:24:08,035 --> 00:24:09,834
Just like the prosecution's seize and search,

350
00:24:09,835 --> 00:24:12,251
one day, I'll make it an important matter.

351
00:24:12,374 --> 00:24:14,517
Well, I need to make a few amendments.

352
00:24:15,305 --> 00:24:18,507
Bit by bit. Darn it, when will I get it done?

353
00:24:18,985 --> 00:24:21,183
You need to find his belongings that the police took.

354
00:24:21,184 --> 00:24:23,459
I'm certain there will be a water bottle among them.

355
00:24:24,055 --> 00:24:27,247
For us to take action, we need proof that he had a disease.

356
00:24:28,225 --> 00:24:30,653
Until two years ago, he received a medical checkup...

357
00:24:30,654 --> 00:24:33,593
to check for the nephrotoxic substance, n-Hexane.

358
00:24:33,594 --> 00:24:36,064
But this year, he didn't receive it. You take care of the rest.

359
00:24:36,065 --> 00:24:37,133
(Medical Checkup Result)

360
00:24:37,134 --> 00:24:38,419
(Harmfulness of n-Hexane discovered. Substituted with IPA)

361
00:24:39,965 --> 00:24:41,403
We can't rule out the possibility of...

362
00:24:41,404 --> 00:24:44,034
paraplegia due to a neurotoxic substance, so...

363
00:24:44,035 --> 00:24:46,014
We need proof first.

364
00:25:11,335 --> 00:25:12,998
Yes, Chief.

365
00:25:13,835 --> 00:25:16,274
We'll investigate the cause thoroughly, sir.

366
00:25:16,275 --> 00:25:17,967
Okay, thank you.

367
00:25:19,404 --> 00:25:21,643
What about Huh Min Ki? Why isn't he coming?

368
00:25:21,644 --> 00:25:22,838
Is he running late again?

369
00:25:24,374 --> 00:25:26,843
- Yes? - Mr. Huh. Where are you?

370
00:25:26,844 --> 00:25:28,784
I'm staking out in front of the police station.

371
00:25:28,785 --> 00:25:30,383
You're just making an excuse for being late...

372
00:25:30,384 --> 00:25:32,923
Look for the water bottle. You won't find it.

373
00:25:32,924 --> 00:25:35,183
- I'll see you later. - Hey!

374
00:25:35,184 --> 00:25:36,928
(List of Police Agency Teams)

375
00:25:41,864 --> 00:25:43,464
This is Seo Jae Yeong of Crime Team 2.

376
00:25:43,465 --> 00:25:45,127
I'm sorry.

377
00:25:45,194 --> 00:25:47,363
I must've called the wrong number.

378
00:25:47,364 --> 00:25:48,904
I'm sorry.

379
00:25:49,874 --> 00:25:52,403
Seo Jae Yeong. Okay.

380
00:25:52,404 --> 00:25:53,843
(Emergency Room Record, Jung Ha Rang)

381
00:25:53,844 --> 00:25:55,508
This is Ha Rang's ER record.

382
00:25:55,975 --> 00:25:58,218
Multiple skin lesions all over his body.

383
00:25:58,614 --> 00:26:00,883
This isn't enough to determine what it is.

384
00:26:00,884 --> 00:26:03,129
We must carry out an autopsy.

385
00:26:03,515 --> 00:26:04,636
Ms. Doh.

386
00:26:05,354 --> 00:26:07,284
I have the results.

387
00:26:07,285 --> 00:26:10,007
We found a tiny bit of organic solvent.

388
00:26:11,654 --> 00:26:13,923
Goodness, this isn't enough to prove he was poisoned.

389
00:26:13,924 --> 00:26:15,353
It's going to be tough.

390
00:26:15,594 --> 00:26:16,992
Of course.

391
00:26:17,634 --> 00:26:20,004
He can't be poisoned just by being exposed at the warehouse.

392
00:26:20,005 --> 00:26:21,834
There must be another way he got exposed.

393
00:26:21,835 --> 00:26:23,574
I'm just checking whether it was there or not.

394
00:26:23,575 --> 00:26:25,889
Okay, fine.

395
00:26:27,174 --> 00:26:29,143
By the way, you can talk to me comfortably.

396
00:26:29,144 --> 00:26:30,368
I'm younger than you.

397
00:26:31,575 --> 00:26:33,726
Oh, I'll take my time.

398
00:26:34,785 --> 00:26:36,141
(Safety First)

399
00:26:36,654 --> 00:26:37,705
Ms. Doh.

400
00:26:42,725 --> 00:26:44,994
(Evidence number 10, 11, 12, 13)

401
00:26:44,995 --> 00:26:46,086
(Evidence number 14)

402
00:26:46,594 --> 00:26:48,054
There's no water bottle.

403
00:26:48,525 --> 00:26:51,193
They probably took it out. I'm certain.

404
00:26:51,194 --> 00:26:53,304
Hey, do you know how difficult it was to take this case?

405
00:26:53,305 --> 00:26:54,304
We don't even have proof.

406
00:26:54,305 --> 00:26:55,504
How can we say they hid the evidence?

407
00:26:55,505 --> 00:26:57,136
They really did hide it.

408
00:26:59,604 --> 00:27:01,440
Hey, are you okay?

409
00:27:02,005 --> 00:27:03,814
Yesterday, I was really...

410
00:27:03,815 --> 00:27:05,274
Goodness.

411
00:27:05,585 --> 00:27:07,523
You worried me sick.

412
00:27:07,585 --> 00:27:08,768
I'm all right.

413
00:27:08,844 --> 00:27:11,453
But what's your issue with that TL bodyguard?

414
00:27:11,454 --> 00:27:13,362
It seemed like he knew you.

415
00:27:15,424 --> 00:27:16,578
Is it a secret?

416
00:27:16,654 --> 00:27:19,193
Wait. Let's talk about that next time.

417
00:27:19,194 --> 00:27:20,623
What do you mean, they hid it?

418
00:27:20,624 --> 00:27:23,294
I saw it with my own two eyes.

419
00:27:23,295 --> 00:27:25,130
There was a water bottle inside his backpack.

420
00:27:25,664 --> 00:27:27,542
My goodness.

421
00:27:29,904 --> 00:27:31,474
Really? Did you take a picture?

422
00:27:31,475 --> 00:27:34,804
If I did, it would already be on the news by now.

423
00:27:34,805 --> 00:27:36,544
Are you sure? You really saw it?

424
00:27:36,545 --> 00:27:38,574
I'm sure, I'm telling you. Wait.

425
00:27:38,575 --> 00:27:41,399
Are you working with us now or is this a temporary thing?

426
00:27:42,414 --> 00:27:45,484
What do you think? Of course, she's working with us.

427
00:27:45,485 --> 00:27:48,748
Goodness. The police have fabricated evidence.

428
00:27:48,755 --> 00:27:50,560
What can we do now?

429
00:27:53,094 --> 00:27:54,216
Why...

430
00:27:55,465 --> 00:27:57,433
do you think I was staking out?

431
00:27:57,434 --> 00:28:01,163
I mean, there was a rookie officer at the police station...

432
00:28:01,164 --> 00:28:02,673
named Seo Jae Yeong.

433
00:28:02,674 --> 00:28:04,403
These type of guys are really determined...

434
00:28:04,404 --> 00:28:06,443
and if we just make up an excuse and give him a slight nudge,

435
00:28:06,444 --> 00:28:08,587
he'll talk about the water bottle.

436
00:28:09,015 --> 00:28:11,113
But will he meet with us?

437
00:28:11,114 --> 00:28:12,943
He won't.

438
00:28:12,944 --> 00:28:16,814
That's why you have to go to the Police Hospital by 9am tomorrow...

439
00:28:16,815 --> 00:28:19,100
and provide orthopedic treatment for outpatients.

440
00:28:20,424 --> 00:28:23,024
It turns out he hurt his arm.

441
00:28:23,025 --> 00:28:25,524
Since he's a cop, he'll go to the Police Hospital.

442
00:28:25,525 --> 00:28:28,217
Finding out the schedule for outpatients...

443
00:28:28,594 --> 00:28:29,663
is a piece of cake.

444
00:28:29,664 --> 00:28:32,868
Hey, don't stare at him. He's showing off again.

445
00:28:33,035 --> 00:28:34,227
That's because I'm really good.

446
00:28:36,174 --> 00:28:39,074
They copied the medical records on the day of the accident.

447
00:28:39,075 --> 00:28:40,304
The corpse is stored safely.

448
00:28:40,305 --> 00:28:42,244
Did you get rid of all his blood and urine?

449
00:28:42,245 --> 00:28:44,613
- Yes. - Then let's stick to the plan.

450
00:28:44,614 --> 00:28:46,175
Call Hanil SD.

451
00:28:46,344 --> 00:28:47,538
Yes, sir.

452
00:29:04,465 --> 00:29:05,587
Yes, Chairman Choi.

453
00:29:06,805 --> 00:29:08,203
Yes, don't worry.

454
00:29:08,204 --> 00:29:10,927
If the public opinion keeps turning against us,

455
00:29:11,775 --> 00:29:13,202
I will get rid of the metro.

456
00:29:14,575 --> 00:29:16,206
We should cut off any risks.

457
00:29:21,222 --> 00:29:22,322
Yes, sir.

458
00:29:22,323 --> 00:29:25,699
Ms. Doh. I think TL has already pulled strings to stop the autopsy.

459
00:29:26,063 --> 00:29:27,766
Ha Rang's mother isn't answering the phone either.

460
00:29:28,262 --> 00:29:30,711
Can you please persuade her?

461
00:29:30,832 --> 00:29:32,873
Okay, I will.

462
00:29:45,583 --> 00:29:46,603
Ma'am.

463
00:29:47,613 --> 00:29:49,255
I have something to tell you.

464
00:29:50,882 --> 00:29:52,178
You can stop now.

465
00:29:53,293 --> 00:29:54,578
You've done enough.

466
00:29:55,663 --> 00:29:57,397
I should hold...

467
00:29:58,392 --> 00:30:00,810
a funeral for my son now and send him off.

468
00:30:05,672 --> 00:30:07,264
We must carry out an autopsy.

469
00:30:12,513 --> 00:30:13,635
Ma'am.

470
00:30:14,242 --> 00:30:15,498
Stop it.

471
00:30:17,613 --> 00:30:20,029
We'll investigate a bit further.

472
00:30:20,652 --> 00:30:21,681
If we can just do an autopsy...

473
00:30:21,682 --> 00:30:26,181
I told you to stop!

474
00:30:27,152 --> 00:30:29,438
I lost my child.

475
00:30:29,593 --> 00:30:33,570
Just stop it already! Stop!

476
00:30:35,932 --> 00:30:38,992
Do you even know how my son died?

477
00:30:39,303 --> 00:30:41,107
But I'm sitting here...

478
00:30:41,833 --> 00:30:44,046
eating when I'm hungry...

479
00:30:44,372 --> 00:30:46,382
and sleeping when I get sleepy.

480
00:30:47,113 --> 00:30:51,938
I've thought about dying hundreds of times.

481
00:31:22,173 --> 00:31:23,181
Ma'am.

482
00:31:23,182 --> 00:31:24,713
Just go.

483
00:31:58,213 --> 00:32:00,048
(Soju)

484
00:32:28,982 --> 00:32:30,309
Please don't say anything to my mom.

485
00:32:31,443 --> 00:32:34,370
She'll just nag me more.

486
00:32:41,593 --> 00:32:42,613
Ha Rang!

487
00:33:01,913 --> 00:33:02,964
Ha Rang.

488
00:33:03,743 --> 00:33:05,344
How did you die?

489
00:33:05,952 --> 00:33:07,881
Do Young, why haven't I heard from you yet?

490
00:33:07,882 --> 00:33:09,616
Did you have a fight?

491
00:33:20,493 --> 00:33:22,291
There were a few people on the platform,

492
00:33:22,292 --> 00:33:24,402
but no one saw the moment of the accident.

493
00:33:24,403 --> 00:33:27,227
There is one person who might have witnessed it.

494
00:33:27,832 --> 00:33:30,171
The yellow shirt. He's holding a camera.

495
00:33:30,172 --> 00:33:32,487
Was the light on the camera flashing?

496
00:33:32,872 --> 00:33:35,272
The light was on. It recorded something.

497
00:33:35,273 --> 00:33:36,915
I have to find that young man.

498
00:33:54,432 --> 00:33:56,132
Ms. Byun, please do me a favor.

499
00:33:56,133 --> 00:33:57,663
I need you to find someone for me.

500
00:34:51,122 --> 00:34:53,265
Listen to my voice.

501
00:35:08,833 --> 00:35:09,871
(Recordings)

502
00:35:09,872 --> 00:35:13,142
(Recorded Calls)

503
00:35:13,143 --> 00:35:15,560
(Police Hospital)

504
00:35:16,283 --> 00:35:18,681
Where do I get my medicine?

505
00:35:18,682 --> 00:35:21,609
Go downstairs to the first floor and get it there.

506
00:35:23,523 --> 00:35:24,982
Thank you.

507
00:35:26,192 --> 00:35:27,722
Mr. Seo Jae Yeong?

508
00:35:32,992 --> 00:35:34,791
This is just a simple survey.

509
00:35:34,792 --> 00:35:37,262
It will be very helpful...

510
00:35:37,263 --> 00:35:39,301
to the Occupational and Environmental Medicine Department...

511
00:35:39,302 --> 00:35:40,871
and their research on officers with posttraumatic stress disorder.

512
00:35:40,872 --> 00:35:42,331
(Where is the water bottle?)

513
00:35:43,502 --> 00:35:44,971
Ta-da!

514
00:35:45,643 --> 00:35:47,651
We're from the UDC.

515
00:35:51,112 --> 00:35:53,255
I don't know what you're talking about.

516
00:35:53,312 --> 00:35:55,851
You guys announced that he was drunk...

517
00:35:55,852 --> 00:35:57,790
to close the case early.

518
00:35:58,153 --> 00:36:01,191
I saw what was in his bag at the emergency room.

519
00:36:01,192 --> 00:36:05,171
I saw he had a water bottle, and I even took pictures.

520
00:36:09,463 --> 00:36:12,871
But I don't think this will end with mere criticism.

521
00:36:12,872 --> 00:36:15,728
I know you're having issues with the prosecution.

522
00:36:17,773 --> 00:36:20,597
I'll call the senior executives. You can talk with them.

523
00:36:22,612 --> 00:36:23,908
Mr. Seo.

524
00:36:24,442 --> 00:36:26,217
Put down your phone.

525
00:36:30,953 --> 00:36:32,044
Hey!

526
00:36:41,932 --> 00:36:43,001
Mr. Seo.

527
00:36:43,002 --> 00:36:46,272
Any patient who comes to the ER has to have their blood tested.

528
00:36:46,273 --> 00:36:49,132
Ha Rang's blood didn't have a drop of alcohol in it.

529
00:36:49,133 --> 00:36:50,871
I'm sure the senior executives would have thought...

530
00:36:50,872 --> 00:36:55,565
it had been disposed since it was at TL Medical Center.

531
00:36:57,112 --> 00:36:59,851
But doctors and medical science...

532
00:36:59,852 --> 00:37:02,464
are true to the rules and principles.

533
00:37:02,752 --> 00:37:03,844
All right?

534
00:37:03,922 --> 00:37:05,513
Wherever you go,

535
00:37:05,583 --> 00:37:08,022
there will always be that one old-fashioned jerk...

536
00:37:08,023 --> 00:37:11,184
who wants to go by the rules.

