Is there a picture of your girlfriend in there or something?

803
00:53:37,682 --> 00:53:39,314
No, of course not.

804
00:53:39,583 --> 00:53:41,082
- Mom. - What?

805
00:53:41,083 --> 00:53:43,979
Can I quit work?

806
00:53:44,383 --> 00:53:45,607
Why? Is it too tough?

807
00:53:46,123 --> 00:53:48,877
Come on. There's no easy job in this world.

808
00:53:49,053 --> 00:53:53,071
Still, there's no reason to do something so exhausting.

809
00:53:55,932 --> 00:53:57,126
Son.

810
00:53:57,532 --> 00:54:00,832
No matter how hard it is, you have to endure it.

811
00:54:00,833 --> 00:54:02,771
You'll get used to it soon.

812
00:54:02,772 --> 00:54:06,572
If you quit because it's too hard, you'll eventually quit again later.

813
00:54:06,573 --> 00:54:09,194
Then you won't be able to do anything.

814
00:54:10,482 --> 00:54:11,533
Okay.

815
00:54:12,043 --> 00:54:13,063
What?

816
00:54:13,442 --> 00:54:15,757
- Fine, I won't quit. - What?

817
00:54:16,553 --> 00:54:18,382
- What? - All right.

818
00:54:18,383 --> 00:54:20,592
- What? - Fine, I'll keep working.

819
00:54:20,593 --> 00:54:22,751
I'll keep working. I'll really try my best.

820
00:54:22,752 --> 00:54:24,092
- I'll work hard. - Really?

821
00:54:24,093 --> 00:54:26,122
All right. I won't quit. Stop it.

822
00:54:26,123 --> 00:54:27,832
Stop it, Mom!

823
00:54:27,833 --> 00:54:29,628
Stop tickling me!

824
00:54:36,532 --> 00:54:37,766
Why did I...

825
00:54:39,172 --> 00:54:42,303
think of my debt at that moment?

826
00:54:43,373 --> 00:54:45,892
When my son was in so much stress.

827
00:54:46,383 --> 00:54:47,434
So...

828
00:54:48,653 --> 00:54:51,951
I told him to just endure it and keep working.

829
00:54:51,952 --> 00:54:54,267
I told him there was no easy job in this world...

830
00:54:54,323 --> 00:54:56,721
and that he should try his best when he had the chance.

831
00:54:56,722 --> 00:54:58,497
That he'd get used to it soon.

832
00:54:59,022 --> 00:55:00,084
So...

833
00:55:02,163 --> 00:55:04,783
I was the one who told him not to quit.

834
00:55:07,532 --> 00:55:08,624
Me.

835
00:55:17,313 --> 00:55:20,082
I was really crazy.

836
00:55:20,083 --> 00:55:21,852
I lost my mind.

837
00:55:21,853 --> 00:55:23,652
I didn't even know...

838
00:55:23,653 --> 00:55:25,897
how hard his job was...

839
00:55:26,752 --> 00:55:28,936
I was crazy.

840
00:55:34,793 --> 00:55:36,332
I was crazy.

841
00:55:36,333 --> 00:55:38,270
I lost my mind.

842
00:55:45,103 --> 00:55:46,193
Ma'am.

843
00:55:49,972 --> 00:55:51,880
I can't agree to an autopsy.

844
00:55:52,383 --> 00:55:53,944
After you left,

845
00:55:54,182 --> 00:55:56,662
I thought it would be the right thing to do,

846
00:55:57,153 --> 00:55:59,569
but I just can't agree to it.

847
00:56:00,182 --> 00:56:01,621
Ms. Doh.

848
00:56:02,053 --> 00:56:03,352
I'm sorry.

849
00:56:03,353 --> 00:56:05,921
This is all my fault.

850
00:56:05,922 --> 00:56:09,062
All I can think of is my dead son.

851
00:56:09,063 --> 00:56:11,409
This is all my fault.

852
00:56:13,563 --> 00:56:16,184
I heard they found the cause of his accident.

853
00:56:16,532 --> 00:56:18,889
Isn't that enough?

854
00:56:19,573 --> 00:56:21,103
I've never...

855
00:56:22,442 --> 00:56:24,043
made him any nice food...

856
00:56:25,343 --> 00:56:28,065
or bought him nice clothes.

857
00:56:29,583 --> 00:56:32,888
He lived such a hard life and had to leave like that.

858
00:56:33,893 --> 00:56:36,552
Just let me send him...

859
00:56:36,553 --> 00:56:38,838
Please let me send him off in peace.

860
00:56:39,692 --> 00:56:42,832
I'm begging you, Ms. Doh.

861
00:56:42,833 --> 00:56:44,464
Okay, ma'am.

862
00:56:47,032 --> 00:56:48,869
I'm sorry.

863
00:56:51,143 --> 00:56:52,673
I'm sorry.

864
00:56:54,613 --> 00:56:56,211
My son.

865
00:56:56,212 --> 00:56:58,630
My baby, Ha Rang.

866
00:56:58,712 --> 00:57:01,100
It's all my fault...

867
00:57:01,883 --> 00:57:03,993
My son...

868
00:57:04,583 --> 00:57:06,623
My son, Ha Rang...

869
00:57:49,692 --> 00:57:50,987
Three years ago,

870
00:57:51,262 --> 00:57:53,632
we saw another Ha Rang.

871
00:57:53,633 --> 00:57:56,332
Yesterday afternoon at Line 2 Guui Station of Seoul Subway,

872
00:57:56,333 --> 00:57:59,842
20-year-old Mr. Kim, who was repairing the screen door,

873
00:57:59,843 --> 00:58:02,872
got stuck between the door and the train and died.

874
00:58:02,873 --> 00:58:05,781
He risked his life to repair the screen door on his own...

875
00:58:05,782 --> 00:58:09,251
and this 19-year-old man met his death alone.

876
00:58:09,252 --> 00:58:10,481
(The late Mr. Kim)

877
00:58:10,482 --> 00:58:12,122
He lived harder than anyone,

878
00:58:12,123 --> 00:58:14,491
but being branded as a temporary worker for a subcontractor...

879
00:58:14,492 --> 00:58:17,021
crushed the bright youth of this 19-year-old man...

880
00:58:17,022 --> 00:58:20,185
and the lives of his family that he left behind.

881
00:58:21,393 --> 00:58:23,332
He could barely eat a cup of noodles...

882
00:58:23,333 --> 00:58:25,461
let alone a proper meal.

883
00:58:25,462 --> 00:58:29,716
His last day was a few hours before his birthday.

884
00:58:30,472 --> 00:58:32,572
If he was alive for seven more hours,

885
00:58:32,573 --> 00:58:34,711
he would have been 20 years old.

886
00:58:34,712 --> 00:58:37,582
But instead of congratulating him, we had to send our condolences.

887
00:58:37,583 --> 00:58:40,912
We still remember that day from three years ago.

888
00:58:40,913 --> 00:58:43,352
The screen door will open.

889
00:58:43,353 --> 00:58:45,521
These doors were made for the safety of our citizens,

890
00:58:45,522 --> 00:58:48,072
but became a door of death in reality.

891
00:58:48,952 --> 00:58:50,921
The safety we enjoyed...

892
00:58:50,922 --> 00:58:53,778
was actually guaranteed by someone else's life.

893
00:58:54,393 --> 00:58:56,231
If the safety of everyone isn't guaranteed,

894
00:58:56,232 --> 00:58:58,854
that means that no one is safe.

895
00:58:59,762 --> 00:59:03,431
We learned that through Mr. Kim's accident.

896
00:59:03,432 --> 00:59:05,171
It's not your fault.

897
00:59:05,172 --> 00:59:06,601
You are right!

898
00:59:06,772 --> 00:59:09,471
Not only are we outsourcing dangerous work, but in reality,

899
00:59:09,472 --> 00:59:12,582
there's a saying that we're actually outsourcing death.

900
00:59:12,583 --> 00:59:15,082
We want to tell all the laborers that passed away...

901
00:59:15,083 --> 00:59:17,123
that it wasn't their fault.

902
00:59:17,252 --> 00:59:19,322
We hope he knew that...

903
00:59:19,323 --> 00:59:23,521
his death at the job site was never his fault.

904
00:59:23,522 --> 00:59:24,622
(I want to live in a safe country where I won't die at work.)

905
00:59:24,623 --> 00:59:26,092
We call him...

906
00:59:26,363 --> 00:59:29,627
Mr. Kim of Guui Station.

